Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories The Family Violence, Child Protection and Sexual Offences Unit in Galeshewe appeals to the community of Galeshewe to assist in tracking down a suspect who allegedly raped a 27 year old woman.The incident allegedly took place on Tuesday, 21 February, at about 10:00.The suspect cornered the victim behind the shopping complex near the St Bonafice School and threatened her with a knife. She was walking from work when she was approached by the suspect, who allegedly grabbed her from behind. He dragged her to a tree and allegedly raped her, Sgt Majang Skalkie said.According to the police description, the suspect is between the ages of 35 and 40, dark in complexion and of slender build. He is approximately 1,7 m tall.Anyone with information regarding the suspect can contact the investigating officer, Det. WO Conrad De Jongh, on 072-869-0378 or 053-807-6161. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.